---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pip = 'pip install columna';
const play = 'columna-server demo --play';
const mcpConfig = `{
  "mcpServers": {
    "columna": { "command": "columna-server", "args": ["demo"] }
  }
}`;
const docker = 'docker run --rm ghcr.io/datumwise/columna-demo demo --play';
---
<BaseLayout title="Install — datumwise">
  <div class="page-head">
    <p class="kicker">Install</p>
    <h1 class="serif">Run it in two minutes.</h1>
    <p class="lede">No signup, no arguments. A clarify, a refuse, and a disclose print on your machine as real wire JSON.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="door">
    <h2 class="serif">Run it — Python</h2>
    <p>One command installs columna-core (the algebra) and columna-server (the wire + demo) — Apache-2.0, on PyPI; each is installable separately.</p>
    <pre class="wire"><code>{pip}
{play}</code></pre>
    <p class="note">The three-mood transcript that prints is the same one this site is built from — generated by running the shipped package.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="door">
    <h2 class="serif">Connect an agent — MCP</h2>
    <p>The demo serves five read-only tools over MCP stdio. To wire it into Claude Desktop, add to <code>claude_desktop_config.json</code>:</p>
    <pre class="wire"><code>{mcpConfig}</code></pre>
    <p class="note">See <a href="https://github.com/datumwise/columna/blob/main/packages/columna-server/demos/mcp_claude_desktop.md" rel="noopener" target="_blank">the full config + a real clarify → refuse → disclose transcript</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="door">
    <h2 class="serif">Run the server — Docker</h2>
    <p>The read-only demo image (also what powers the live demo endpoint):</p>
    <pre class="wire"><code>{docker}</code></pre>
    <p class="note">Serves only the packaged demo Manifold; read-only by construction.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="door">
    <h2 class="serif">Or just watch it run</h2>
    <p>The live demo on this site executes the same package against a hosted endpoint — <a href="/#exhibit-b">see the four moods on the homepage ↓</a>.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head h1 { font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin: 0.3rem 0 0.8rem; }
  .lede { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 34rem; }
  .door { margin: 2.6rem 0; }
  .door h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0 0 0.6rem; }
  .door p { font-size: 0.98rem; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0.5rem 0; }
  .door .note { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--ink-faint); }
  .door code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85em; background: var(--paper-raised); padding: 0.1em 0.35em; border-radius: 4px; }
  pre.wire { background: var(--wire-bg); color: var(--wire-ink); padding: 1rem 1.15rem; border-radius: 8px;
    overflow-x: auto; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.84rem; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0.8rem 0; }
  /* the pre owns the styling; reset the inline-.door code chip so it doesn't tint the block */
  pre.wire code { font-family: inherit; background: none; padding: 0; border-radius: 0; color: inherit; }
</style>
